node.text:
Based on a threat-informed, ten-year time horizon, the Marine Corps is designing a force for naval expeditionary warfare in actively contested spaces. Throughout this ten-year initiative, the Marine Corps will make investments in capabilities to include long range precision fires, advanced reconnaissance capabilities, unmanned systems, and resilient networks. (U.S. Marine Corps video by Cpl. Nicholas Filca)

For more information, view the link in the bio.

#OTD, we recognize Sgt Robert O’Malley, whose actions against enemy forces as part of Operation Starlite in 1965 would lead him to become the conflict’s first Marine Corps Medal of Honor recipient. Sgt O’Malley’s frontline leadership, and complete devotion to his Marines, demonstrates the definition of a true Fighter-Leader. Semper Fidelis.

#MedalofHonor #VietnamWar #Marines #USMCHistory #ValuesInAction

node.text:
@USNavy and #Marines deployed a Navy Marine Expeditionary Ship Interdiction System (NMESIS) to participate in Large Scale Exercise 21 (LSE 21) at Pacific Missile Range Facility Barking Sands, Hawaii, August 15. 

During the training, a Marine Corps fires Expeditionary Advanced Base (EAB) sensed, located, identified and struck a target ship at sea more than 100 nautical miles away.

The live-fire sinking exercise demonstrated a Marine fires EAB’s ability to sense, target and strike a target at sea, providing sea control or contributing to sea denial in fleet operations. 

The Marine Corps’ #ForceDesign2030 centers on Marines providing long-range precision strike capabilities as a stand-in force during littoral operations in a contested environment. 

@pacificmarines

#FreeAndOpenIndoPacific #BlueGreenTeam #LSE21 

(U.S. Marine Corps photos by Lance Cpl. Dillon Buck)

(U.S. Navy photo by Mass Communication Specialist 1st Class David Mora Jr.

Marines already on the ground are providing security at Hamid Karzai International Airport as well as non-combatant evacuation operation support.  These are core missions for Marine Corps forward-deployed forces.

#OTD in 1918, Opha May Johnson became the first woman to be sworn in the Marine Corps. She, along with her 304 other colleagues, pioneered the way for generations of women who have earned the lifelong title of Marine. Semper Fidelis. 

#Marines #USMC #USMCHistory #TheFewTheProud

node.text:
Offensive Operations ☠️

Lance Cpl. Gavin Wright, a rifleman with @3dmardiv, conducts offensive operations on key maritime terrain during Large Scale Exercise 2021 on @mcb_hawaii. 

#LSE21 is based on a progression of scenarios that will assess and refine modern warfare concepts, including Distributed Maritime Operations (DMO), Expeditionary Advanced Base Operations (EABO), and Littoral Operations in a Contested Environment (LOCE). 

LSE 2021 is the first iteration of what will become a triennial exercise with plans for future iterations to include partners and allies from around the world. 

#Maritime #JointForce #USMC 

(U.S. Marine Corps photos by Cpl. Alexis Moradian)
